name: CryptoMushrooms #003 - Amanita Muscaria
description:
One of the most iconic toadstool species, also know as "Fly Agaric" or "Fly Amanita", is a large conspicuous mushroom and its red cap with white warts are a vivid contrast against the green and brown of the birch and pine forests where it grows. Usually found in forests during wet periods in summer and autumn, generally as a symbiont with pine and birch plantations, it associates with various deciduous and coniferous trees. Is often referred to as a “magic mushroom”, but compared to psilocybin-containing mushrooms the effects are very different, because it does not contain psilocybin or psilocin. It contains some pharmacologically active alkaloids, including muscarine, ibotenic acid and muscimol, causing a sedative, depressant, and deliriant effect.
